{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:13:04.730699+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my analysis of the repository, here are the setup and day-to-day development commands for this Vue.js 3 + Vite project:\n\n## Project Setup\n\n**Node.js version**: 24 (as specified in `.nvmrc`)\n\n**Package manager**: pnpm 10.20.0 (enforced via `preinstall` script)\n\n## Commands\n\n### Install dependencies\n```bash\npnpm install\n```\n\n### Development server\n```bash\npnpm run dev\n```\nThis starts the Vite development server with hot-reload.\n\n### Build for production\n```bash\npnpm run build\n```\nCompiles and minifies the application for production deployment.\n\n### Unit tests\n```bash\npnpm run test:unit\n```\nRuns the test suite using Vitest.\n\n### Unit tests with coverage\n```bash\npnpm run test:unit-coverage\n```\nRuns tests and generates coverage reports.\n\n### Linting\n```bash\npnpm run lint\n```\nRuns ESLint on all `.vue`, `.ts`, and `.js` files.\n\n### Linting and fixing\n```bash\npnpm run lint-fix\n```\nRuns ESLint with auto-fix capabilities.\n\n### Preview production build\n```bash\npnpm run preview\n```\nPreviews the production build locally.\n\n### Build and preview\n```bash\npnpm run build-preview\n```\nBuilds for production and then starts the preview server.\n\n## Additional Notes\n\n- The project uses semantic-release for automated versioning\n- Commitlint is configured for conventional commit messages\n- Husky is set up for Git hooks\n- Lint-staged is configured to run linters on staged files before commits\n\nThese commands provide a complete development workflow from setup through testing and production builds.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 589, "prompt_tokens": 9108, "total_tokens": 9697, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 218, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 